<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis box="[199,365,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,151,176]" name="Malta" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
. Pygofer in lateral view longer than its height, posterior margin broadly rounded, macrosetae confined to posterior half. Valve 
<taxonomicName box="[525,634,188,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
with conically rounded posterior margin, 
<number box="[1111,1146,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="1.8">1.8</number>
times as broad at base as long medially. Subgenital plate with well defined posterior fingerlike process 
<number box="[1018,1067,224,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="0.3">0.30</number>
times total length, lateral margin less strongly convex. Style twice as long as broad at base, with slender, slightly laterally curved apophysis, subapical lobe well defined. Connective with stem 
<number box="[741,776,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times length of arms. Aedeagus without basal processes; dorsal apodeme well developed; each shaft divergent from base in posterior view, broadened distally and apices tightly curved inwardly; in lateral view shafts appearing lamellate and curved anteriorly, apices rounded; gonopore almost at midlength of each shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
