<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,511,536]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,509,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonaparensis">
<emphasis box="[325,509,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">H. sonaparensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[641,793,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayarami">
<emphasis box="[641,793,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">H. mayarami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of male genitalia, but differs in having strongly inwardly curved apices of aedeagal shafts and a slender apex of the apophysis of the style.
</paragraph>
